data['Ram'] = data['Ram'].str.replace('GB','').astype('int32')
    ## data['Ram']: truy cp vo ct 'Ram' ca 'data'
        ## loi b k t 'GB' (s dng phng thc replace  thay th k t 'GB' bng k t rng)
        ## p kiu d liu 'int32' bng phng thc astype()
data['Weight'] = data['Weight'].str.replace('kg','').astype('float32')
    ## data['Weight']: truy cp vo ct 'Weight' ca 'data'
        ## loi b k t 'kg' (s dng phng thc replace  thay th k t 'kg' bng k t rng)
        ## p kiu d liu 'float32' bng phng thc astype()
data['Price'] = data['Price'].astype(int)
    ## p kiu d liu 'int'

data['Touchscreen']=data['ScreenResolution'].apply(lambda x:1 if 'Touchscreen' in x else 0)
    ## to mt ct mi 'Touchscreen' trong DataFrame 'data' , dng  ch ra liu mi mu c s dng mn hnh cm ng (touchscreen) hay khng. C th, cc gi tr tr v bao gm
        ## 1: c cm ng 'Touchscreen'
        ## 0: khng c cm ng 'Non-Touchscreen'
    ## data['ScreenResolution']: truy cp vo ct 'ScreenResolution' trong DataFrame 'data',  ly thng tin v  phn gii mn hnh ca mi mu
    ## apply(): p dng mt hm 'lambda' cho mi phn t trong ct 'ScreenResolution' ca DataFrame 'data' ,kim tra xem chui 'Touchscreen' c xut hin trong mi phn t ca ct 'ScreenResolution' hay khng
        ## lambda x: 1 if 'Touchscreen' in x else 0: Hm ny kim tra xem chui 'Touchscreen' c xut hin trong chui x
        ## Nu c 'Touchscreen', hm tr v 1, ngc li tr v 0

## Hm fetch_processor c nh ngha  xc nh loi CPU da trn thng tin v CPU c cung cp di dng chui
## text: i din cho chui m t loi CPU.
def fetch_processor(text):
    if text =='Intel Core i5' or text  == 'Intel Core i7' or text == 'Intel Core i3':
        return text
    
        ## kim tra xem 'text' c phi l mt trong cc loi CPU Intel ph bin nh 'Intel Core i5', 'Intel Core i7', hoc 'Intel Core i3' hay khng
        ## Nu c, hm tr v chnh chui text  bng phng thc 'return'
    else:
        if text.split()[0] == 'Intel':
            return 'Other Intel Processor'
        
            ## Nu text khng thuc vo bt k loi CPU Intel no trong iu kin trn, hm s tip tc kim tra xem chui bt u bng 'Intel' hay khng ( xc nh xem c phi l mt loi CPU Intel khc khng)
            ## Nu phn t u tin ca 'text' l 'Intel', hm s tr v chui 'Other Intel Processor'
            
        else:
            return 'AMD Processor'
        
            ## Nu chui 'text' khng phi l mt loi CPU Intel, hm s tr v chui 'AMD Processor'  biu din loi CPU ny

        return 'Other/Linux/No OS'

step1 = ColumnTransformer(transformers=[
    ('col_tnf',OneHotEncoder(sparse=False,drop='first'),[0,1,7,10,11])
],remainder='passthrough')

    ## ColumnTransformer(): p dng OneHotEncoder  thc hin cc bin i d liu cho cc ct c index=[0,1,7,10,11]
    ## remainder='passthrough': Cc ct cn li s c b qua v truyn qua m khng bin i
    ## 'col_tnf': tn ca bin i
    ## OneHotEncoder(sparse=False,drop='first'): b bin i (m ha One-Hot) cho cc ct c ch s 0, 1, 7, 10, 11
    ## drop='first': loi b ct u tin sau khi m ha
    ## sparse=False: m bo rng kt qu tr v s khng phi l mt ma trn tha (sparse matrix) m l mt mng NumPy dy c
    
step2 = LinearRegression()
    ## khi to mt m hnh hi quy tuyn tnh bng hm LinearRegression()
pipe = Pipeline([
    ('step1',step1),
    ('step2',step2)
])
    ## to Pipeline  kt hp cc bc x l d liu v m hnh ML bng phng thc Pipeline()
        ## step1 (ColumnTransformer) v step2 (LinearRegression) c kt hp  to thnh mt pipeline

pipe.fit(x_train,y_train)
    ## hun luyn m hnh trn d liu hun luyn (x_train v y_train) bng phng thc fit()
y_pred = pipe.predict(x_test)
    ## d on gi tr ca bin mc tiu 'y_pred' t d liu kim tra 'x_test' bng phng thc predict()
    
# scores.append(r2_score(y_test,y_pred))
print("r2 Score ",r2_score(y_test,y_pred))
    ## tnh im R^2, nh gi mc  ph hp ca m hnh vi d liu kim tra bng phng thc r2_score (Kt qu cng gn 1 th hin m hnh d on tt hn)
    ## Sau  in ra mn hnh chui "r2 Score " v kt qu tnh c pha di
print("MAE Score ",mean_absolute_error(y_test,y_pred))
    ## tnh sai s trung bnh tuyt i gia gi tr d on v gi tr thc t, nh gi  chnh xc ca m hnh hi quy bng phng thc mean_absolute_error
    ## Sau  in ra mn hnh chui "MAE Score " v kt qu tnh c pha di

    ## OneHotEncoder(sparse=False,drop='first'): b bin i (m ha One-Hot) cho cc ct c ch s 0, 1, 7, 10, 11

    ## sparse=False: m bo rng kt qu tr v s khng phi l mt ma trn tha (sparse matrix) m l mt mng NumPy dy c

step2 = Ridge(alpha=10)
    ## To mt m hnh hi quy Ridge vi tham s alpha c t l 10, sau  gn vo bin 'step2'
pipe = Pipeline([
    ('step1',step1),
    ('step2',step2)
])
    ## to Pipeline  kt hp cc bc x l d liu v m hnh ML bng phng thc Pipeline()
        ## step1 (ColumnTransformer) v step2 (m hnh hi quy Ridge) c kt hp  to thnh mt pipeline

pipe.fit(x_train,y_train)
    ## hun luyn m hnh trn d liu hun luyn (x_train v y_train) bng phng thc fit()
y_pred = pipe.predict(x_test)
    ## d on gi tr ca bin mc tiu 'y_pred' t d liu kim tra 'x_test' bng phng thc predict()

print("r2 Score ",r2_score(y_test,y_pred))
    ## tnh im R^2, nh gi mc  ph hp ca m hnh vi d liu kim tra bng phng thc r2_score (Kt qu cng gn 1 th hin m hnh d on tt hn)
    ## Sau  in ra mn hnh chui "r2 Score " v kt qu tnh c pha di
print("MAE Score ",mean_absolute_error(y_test,y_pred))
    ## tnh sai s trung bnh tuyt i gia gi tr d on v gi tr thc t, nh gi  chnh xc ca m hnh hi quy bng phng thc mean_absolute_error
